						<div class="postbody">My program <a href="http://zzo38computer.org/prog/utftovlq.zip" class="postlink">utftovlq</a> can do that; use <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">utftovlq wW</tt> to swap endianness of 16-bit words (you can also swap 32-bit words with <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">utftovlq dD</tt>, but not 24-bit) (Windows executable is not provided, but you could compile it yourself)</div>

					
