					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">You can do this pretty easily with Python (free and open source) with something like this for 16-bit words:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">with open('input.bin', 'rb') as input_file, open('output.bin', 'wb') as output_file:<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;data = input_file.read()<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;for i in range(0, len(data), 2):<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;high = data&#91;i&#93;<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;low = data&#91;i + 1&#93;<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;output_file.write(low)<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;output_file.write(high)<br /></div><br /><br />In fact, you can extend it to work with an arbitrary word size like this:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">input_file_name = 'input.bin'<br />output_file_name = 'output.bin'<br />word_size = 2<br /><br />with open(input_file_name, 'rb') as input_file, open(output_file_name, 'wb') as output_file:<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; while True:<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; word = input_file.read(word_size)<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; if not word:<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; break<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; output_file.write(word&#91;::-1&#93;)<br /></div></div>

					
